   Container life cycle 
================

	Ø docker ps :- it will show you only running containers
	Ø docker ps -a:- it will show you all containers including stopped containers
	Ø docker build:- it is for building a image
	Ø docker images:- to see images
	Ø docker run :-  it will pull the image form registry, secondly it will create container and finally it will start container
	Ø docker stop :- it is for to stop any running container
	Ø docker restart :- to restarting the container
	Ø docker rm :- to remove or delete only stopped contianers
	Ø docker rm -f :- To delete or remove running containers
	Ø Docker rmi:- to delete images
	Ø docker pause:- to pause a container
	Ø docker unpause:- to unpause a paused contianer
	Ø docker exec -it:- to login into the container
	Ø docker inspect: -to know or get all details of ur container
	Ø Curl :- to check whether the app or container is working properly or not
	Ø docker rm $(docker ps -aq) :- to delete all stopped containers
	Ø docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq) :- To  delete all containers including stopped and running containers.
docker rmi $(docker images -q):- To delete all images at a time

